{#
  hx-theme — Drupal Twig Template
  =================================

  Wraps a content region in <hx-theme> to scope design tokens to that subtree.

  IMPORTANT: hx-theme requires JavaScript to inject --hx-* design tokens.
  Server-rendered content is accessible before hydration, but visual theming
  (colors, typography, spacing via tokens) is applied client-side. Ensure
  meaningful fallback styles exist in your base CSS for the no-JS case.

  system mode (window.matchMedia) is NOT available during Drupal server-side
  rendering. Always set theme explicitly from PHP/Twig. Use theme="auto" if you
  want OS preference to apply after client-side hydration without a JS cookie/session.

  Parameters:
    theme      (string)  Required. One of: 'light' | 'dark' | 'high-contrast' | 'auto'.
                         Defaults to 'light'.
                         - 'light'         — Light token set (default).
                         - 'dark'          — Dark token set.
                         - 'high-contrast' — WCAG 7:1+ contrast token set. Use for
                                             users with low vision or HC display modes.
                         - 'auto'          — Reads OS color-scheme preference after hydration.
                                             Renders as 'light' until JavaScript runs.
    attributes (object)  Optional. Additional HTML attributes spread onto <hx-theme>.

  Usage — Full page theming:
    Read theme preference from Drupal config, cookie, or user profile:

    {% set active_theme = user.field_preferred_theme.value|default('light') %}
    {% include '@mytheme/hx-theme/hx-theme.twig' with {
      theme: active_theme,
    } %}
      {{ page.content }}
    {% endinclide %}

  Usage — Dark sidebar inside a light page (nested scope):
    <hx-theme theme="light">
      {{ page.content }}
      <hx-theme theme="dark">
        {{ page.sidebar_first }}
      </hx-theme>
    </hx-theme>

  Usage — Theme toggle button (Drupal behavior):
    Add data-hx-theme-toggle="dark" to any clickable element. The behavior below
    finds the nearest <hx-theme> ancestor and updates its theme attribute:

      (function (Drupal, once) {
        Drupal.behaviors.helixTheme = {
          attach: function (context) {
            once('hx-theme-toggle', '[data-hx-theme-toggle]', context).forEach((btn) => {
              btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
                const themeEl = btn.closest('hx-theme') || document.querySelector('hx-theme');
                if (themeEl) {
                  themeEl.setAttribute('theme', btn.dataset.hxThemeToggle);
                }
              });
            });
          },
        };
      })(Drupal, once);

  Registration:
    Load the component script in your theme's .libraries.yml:
      hx-theme:
        js:
          path/to/@helixui/library/dist/hx-theme.js: { attributes: { type: module } }
        dependencies:
          - core/drupal
          - core/once

    Attach the library in page.html.twig:
      {{ attach_library('mytheme/hx-theme') }}
#}

<hx-theme
  theme="{{ theme|default('light') }}"
  {% for key, val in attributes|default({}) %}{{ key }}="{{ val }}" {% endfor %}
>
  {% block content %}{% endblock %}
</hx-theme>
